-- Stocks Pare Losses, Led by Increases in Essar Energy, Standard Chartered
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-10-12T15:02:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/stocks-pare-losses-led-by-increases-in-essar-energy-standard-chartered.html
U.K. stocks pared losses, led by
gains in Essar Energy Plc and Standard Chartered Plc.  The FTSE 100 Index fell less than 0.1 perecent to 5,670.254
at 3:57 p.m. in London. The gauge earlier fell as much as 1.3
percent.  Essar,  an Indian power generator and refiner, rose 3.1
percent to 498.3 pence while Standard Chartered, which generates
more than half of its revenue in Asia, gained 2.5 percent to
1,916.5 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
